{"_id": "322c3978a670d51e", "name": "Athletics", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "STR+DEX", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Athletics covers a range of physical activities, including climbing, jumping, throwing, and running. Skill rolls for any of these activities are handled by a single roll against the Athletics skill.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "d703c018b276b2c6", "name": "Boating", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "STR+CON", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "The Boating skill covers the operation of small floating craft on rivers, lakes, and close inshore. Appropriate vessels are generally boats, canoes, or rafts unsuited to the rigours of the open sea. Ships with large crews or designed for long overseas journeys are covered under the Seamanship Professional Skill.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "48518af4e5d8eaf4", "name": "Brawn", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "STR+SIZ", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Brawn is the efficient application of technique when applying raw physical force. The skill covers acts of applied might, including lifting, breaking down doors and contests of strength.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "9108f1010f75a999", "name": "Conceal", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "DEX+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Conceal is the counterpoint to Stealth, being the concealment of large objects rather than the character themselves. It is versatile in application, from hiding a scroll in a library to disguising the presence of a trap or secret passage.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "f5cd8cef2bae5bd8", "name": "Customs", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "INT*2+40", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Customs represents the character's knowledge of their own community: its social codes, rites, rituals, taboos, and so on. The skill is used when it is essential to accurately interpret or perform any socially important custom or to behave in a particular way. Includes a static +40% bonus.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "7ae5eb054903e957", "name": "Dance", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "DEX+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Just about every culture uses dance in some way \u2014 either as recreation or as part of important rituals. The Dance skill measures a character's ability to move rhythmically and accurately when called upon to do so.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "a713229c85ac0832", "name": "Deceit", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "INT+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Deceit covers all instances where a character attempts to mask the truth and offer a deception of some kind: barefaced lying, misleading a guard, or bluffing during a card game. Deceit forms a counterpart to the Insight skill and can be used to oppose Insight rolls when others are attempting to discern either truth or motive.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "f2c6151d6c0d99f3", "name": "Drive", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "DEX+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Drive covers the control of wheeled or drawn vehicles, whether by beasts of burden or powered by more esoteric means, such as chariots, sleds, sail carts, or gasoline cars. A roll is also necessary if the vehicle is powered by a means different than the driver is used to.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "513f6dc0ecee2e56", "name": "Endurance", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "CON*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Endurance is a character's capacity to endure physical stress, pain, and fatigue. It is a general gauge of resilience, stamina, and metabolism, and is used most specifically to resist the possible effects of injuries, including harmful poisons and disease.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "fcebb8bec493a667", "name": "Evade", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "DEX*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Evade is used to escape from observed, impending danger \u2014 against ranged weapons, avoiding traps, changing the engagement distance in combat, and generally getting out of the way of physical hazards. It can also be used as a resistance roll for certain types of magic. Using Evade usually leaves the character prone.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "ac8e90f5654ed9af", "name": "First Aid", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "INT+DEX", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "The skill of First Aid measures a character's ability to treat minor injuries and stabilise more severe ones. First Aid may be applied only once per specific injury and heals 1d3 points of damage.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "d35a98028cca23c2", "name": "Influence", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "CHA*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Influence is a measurement of a character's ability to persuade others, through personal charisma, into a desired way of behaving. It is used in a wide variety of situations, from changing someone's mind to bribing an official or guard. Influence rolls are typically opposed by the Perception, Willpower, or another Influence skill.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "9e1c9c294ec3f4b9", "name": "Insight", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "INT+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Insight is the ability to read or intuitively define another's verbal and non-verbal behaviour to establish their motives and state of mind. Insight is used to determine whether someone is telling a lie (opposed by the other person's Deceit skill), or to predict how someone feels about a particular situation.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "911f0f24bdce6808", "name": "Locale", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Locale measures a character's understanding of local flora, fauna, terrain, and weather in the area where they have spent much of their life. The character knows the common plants, trees, and animals, their properties and behaviour, where to find shelter, the likely weather for the season, and the most common regional dangers. In unfamiliar locations Locale should be made one or more grades harder.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "ff7932e1d2213be3", "name": "Native Tongue", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "INT+CHA+40", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Native Tongue is the ability to speak and read one's own language, measuring articulation, eloquence, and the depth of the speaker's vocabulary. Unlike other skills, Native Tongue is not rolled against directly but is treated as a static representation of overall fluency, limiting the level of conversational interaction. Includes a static +40% bonus.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "da1691c28eb331e4", "name": "Perception", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "INT+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Perception is used for both passive observation and focused detection; whether hunting for something specific, a general scan of an area, or simple awareness of surroundings. Specific conditions \u2014 such as darkness \u2014 may affect the Difficulty Grade of the skill roll depending on the primary senses being used.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "fcf46fae32b17897", "name": "Ride", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "DEX+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Ride covers the ability to control and remain mounted on those creatures that are trained to be ridden. It can be applied to a diverse range of beasts, from mules to elephants; even flying or swimming creatures such as giant eagles or dolphins. Riding an unfamiliar species is always one Difficulty Grade harder.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "283973714cfcfb1f", "name": "Sing", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "CHA+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Carrying a tune is covered by Sing, anything from monotonous chants through to complex arias. The skill reflects the user's ability to maintain rhythm, keep in key, and remember the correct words.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "899db408cba5858a", "name": "Stealth", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "DEX+INT", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Hiding out of plain sight, or moving with minimal sound, are covered by the Stealth skill. Cover and conditions such as darkness or loud background noise improve the grade of the skill. A warrior wearing heavy armour can conceal themselves behind a wall if they stand still, but moving quickly might cause their armour to jingle.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "d0d933facd58904b", "name": "Swim", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "STR+CON", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Without development, the ability to swim is limited to keeping one's head above water for a short time. Higher Swim percentages indicate being able to negotiate deeper and stronger waters with less risk of drowning. Rough seas, strong currents, and rip tides all reduce the grade of the skill.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "3a6cc9e7bc2014e1", "name": "Unarmed", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "STR+DEX", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Unarmed is a universal Combat Skill common to all characters, measuring the ability to defend oneself without weapons. The Unarmed skill covers the brawling and wrestling techniques known by that culture. As a Combat Skill, its Critical and Fumble effects are covered by the rules for combat.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "5b388583a8c29ad0", "name": "Willpower", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "standard", "baseFormula": "POW*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Willpower is a measure of a character's ability to concentrate, channel their force of will in a particular direction, or harden their psyche to possible mental shock. It is used in all manner of situations where mental resilience is required, and includes resisting magic.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
